REV(1)                     User Commands                    REV(1)

NNAAMMEE
       rev - reverse lines characterwise

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       rreevv [option] [_f_i_l_e...]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The rreevv utility copies the specified files to standard out‐
       put, reversing the order of characters in every  line.   If
       no files are specified, standard input is read.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --VV, ----vveerrssiioonn
              Display version information and exit.

       --hh, ----hheellpp
              Display help text and exit.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ttaacc(1)

AAVVAAIILLAABBIILLIITTYY
       The  rev  command  is part of the util-linux package and is
       available from Linux Kernel Archive ⟨https://www.kernel.org
       /pub/linux/utils/util-linux/⟩.

util-linux                September 2011                    REV(1)
